\begin_layout Subsection*
The minimalistic DP of a buyer
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
While the simple action space needs not be further simplified (except for
 some upper bound of 
\begin_inset Formula $v$
\end_inset

), and the distribution of 
\begin_inset Formula $D_{R,v}$
\end_inset

 may, with certain licence, be viewed as not depending on 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

, the variable 
\begin_inset Formula $C_{R,v}$
\end_inset

 does depend on 
\begin_inset Formula $R$
\end_inset

 (clearly 
\begin_inset Formula $C$
\end_inset

 will be different for 
\begin_inset Formula $a=10$
\end_inset

 from that given 
\begin_inset Formula $a=100$
\end_inset

).
 Consequently, any approximation of 
\begin_inset Formula $V$
\end_inset

 has to take at least 
\begin_inset Formula $a$
\end_inset

 into account.
 Reflecting the fact that, with increasing volume, the price becomes higher,
 we can assume 
\begin_inset Formula $C$
\end_inset

 to be convex in 
\begin_inset Formula $v$
\end_inset

, we can approximate 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
C_{R,v}=C_{a,v}=a+f(vE)
\]

\end_inset

Further, we approximate 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
D_{R,v}\doteq vE.
\]

\end_inset

Here, 
